This is similar to finding the number of "valid" dates where the entire 8-digit number has even parity for each digit. This is analogous to a binary matrix where each row represents a date, and each column represents a digit, with a 1 indicating the presence of the digit. We need the sum of each column to be even, which is a classic problem in combinatorics. In coding theory, this is similar to finding the number of codewords in a binary linear code with certain parity-check conditions. However, the number of such codewords can be calculated as 2^{n - k}, where n is the number of variables and k is the number of constraints
